  "prompt": "Why is OTG not working properly for hard disk on Android Nougat?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why OTG (On-The-Go) is not working properly for a hard disk on Android Nougat:\n\n1. Compatibility issues:\n- Some Android Nougat devices may have limited OTG support\n- Specific hard disk or USB drive might not be fully compatible\n- Older device with older USB controller\n\n2. Power requirements:\n- Hard disk may require more power than device can provide\n- External power adapter might be necessary\n- Some devices have limited USB power output\n\n3. File system limitations:\n- Unsupported file system format (NTFS, exFAT)\n- Android Nougat might have restricted file system support\n- Need to format hard disk to FAT32 or ext4\n\n4. Software/driver problems:\n- Outdated OTG drivers\n- System software incompatibility\n- Need to update Android version or firmware\n\n5. Device settings:\n- OTG might be disabled in device settings\n- Insufficient system permissions\n- USB debugging not enabled\n\nTroubleshooting steps:\n- Use powered USB hub\n- Check file system compatibility\n- Update device firmware\n- Try different USB OTG cable\n- Verify device's OTG support specifications",
